### UX Constraints — Observatory (HN-Facing)

```
CONSTRAINT                              │ RATIONALE                    │ PRIORITY
────────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────┼─────────
ZERO newsletter popups                  │ Instant credibility kill     │ HARD
ZERO cookie banners beyond legal min.   │ Friction = bounce            │ HARD
Fast load: <2s first contentful paint   │ HN audience has zero patience│ HARD
Content above the fold immediately      │ No splash pages, no hero imgs│ HARD
All sources inline and clickable        │ They WILL check              │ HARD
Dark mode support                       │ Expected by this audience    │ HIGH
Print/PDF stylesheet that works         │ People want to save analysis │ HIGH
Monospace for data tables and code      │ Visual trust signal          │ HIGH
No social share buttons on page body    │ Clutter tax; they share URLs │ HIGH
Dense text OK — do NOT simplify         │ Respects intelligence        │ HIGH
No animations that delay content access │ Substance over style         │ HIGH
Methodology visible without clicking    │ Front and center, not hidden │ HIGH
Mobile-responsive but desktop-optimized │ HN browses on desktop        │ MEDIUM
Discussion link to HN thread            │ Community expects it         │ MEDIUM
Anchor links for every section/heading  │ HN comments reference sections│ MEDIUM
View source reveals clean, semantic HTML│ Audience inspects code       │ MEDIUM
No tracking beyond minimal analytics    │ Privacy-conscious audience   │ MEDIUM
RSS feed for updates                    │ HN audience uses RSS         │ MEDIUM
```

