## Content Tailoring by Audience

The same underlying analysis gets presented differently depending on entry point:

| Content Element | HN (Entry) | Teacher (Entry) | Academic (Entry) | Voter (Conversion) | Politician (Target) |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Differential diagnosis | Full analysis with scoring tables | Simplified "competing explanations" | Full analysis + methodology appendix | Irrelevant — already convinced | Irrelevant — too academic |
| ICESCR articles | Linked from analysis | Lesson plans per article | Cross-referenced with legal commentary | "This right affects you because..." | "This treaty protects X" (one line) |
| Higher-order effects | Full cascade visualization | "What happens next?" discussion | Formal chain analysis | "Here's what happens without this" | 60-second floor speech version |
| Action items | Template letters, senator lookup | Civic participation lesson plan | Policy brief format | **Primary content**: senator lookup + template + 5-min CTA | Policy brief + political cover |
| Political cover | Implicit in analysis quality | Implicit in materials quality | Citation-worthy methodology | "173 nations including all NATO allies" | **Primary content**: who else, what risk, what cover |
| Tagline | "HRO, Hacker News Edition" | "Classroom Resources" | "Research and Methodology" | "5 minutes. Your senator. 173 nations." | "Bipartisan. Standard RUDs. Allied consensus." |

