## Success Metrics (Added 2026-03-04)

Extracted from external marketing strategy review. Metrics organized by what Cloudflare Web Analytics can surface vs. what requires manual observation.

### Trackable via Cloudflare Web Analytics
- **Time on educational content** — pages like /covenant/articles/*, /educators, /connection/* (indicates depth of engagement)
- **Return visitor rates** — repeat visits signal trust and ongoing value
- **Referrer diversity** — organic sharing shows up as direct or social referrers beyond initial HN spike
- **Geographic distribution** — international interest validates the global framing
- **Page flow** — entry → /action conversion path (do visitors reach the advocacy toolkit?)

### Observable via External Signals
- **Organic sharing** — Bluesky reposts, Lemmy upvotes, citation in other publications
- **Academic citations** — Google Scholar mentions of unratified.org or methodology
- **Media mentions** — press coverage citing the AI-ICESCR connection
- **Educator adoption** — download patterns for print resources, educator hub traffic
- **Community engagement depth** — GitHub Issues, Discussions, blog post PRs

### Not Yet Trackable (Deferred)
- User feedback on feeling respected and informed (requires survey mechanism)
- Policy influence measurement (requires tracking legislative activity)
- Cross-platform ecosystem health (requires unified analytics across 3 sites)

